Dayo Ojerinde The Group Business Manager, Lagos and Ogun states, Emzor Pharmaceutical Industries, Mrs Chinyere Kelvin, has urged Nigerians to adhere to protective measures put in place by the Federal Government and relevant health agencies to stop the spread of COVID-19. Kelvin, in a statement, said the company had unveiled a COVID-19 Response Programmme, tagged, ‘Emzor Cares’, in response to the community transmission phase of the coronavirus pandemic in the country. “The programme comprises a series of interventions to complement the various measures of Government and create the much-needed succour at various touch points with the public. “We are also playing a supporting role by continuing production in our factories, providing health care products to Nigerians during this pandemic. Our goal is to continue to keep Nigerians safe by providing immune-boosting medications like vitamins, supplements and nutritional oils. “The Emzor Cares Initiative is consistent with our commitment to continue to provide products with consistently high quality, made readily available at prices which create value for all stakeholders. We urge Nigerians to continue to stay safe and adhere to the protective measures put in place by the government and health agencies,” Kelvin said. She added that the initiative demonstrated the company’s support and celebration of the frontline workers. Copyright PUNCH.
